$interpreted: Bandit: You're...Aosta, the doctor without a license, right?
Aosta: Who are you?
Bandit: Since I was bitten by a monster, I started to feel ill. It's getting more and more serious by the second. Please save me!
Aosta: How does that benefit me?
Bandit: I-I don't have money, but I do have some information that you may be interested in...
Bandit: Thank you.
Aosta: Tell me everything you know.
Bandit: In the past, I...used to be a criminal of Kingdom of the Sun. I was enslaved and sent to a very scary place to mine.
Aosta: Atlas, I presume?
Bandit: When the Atlas void is in a state of inhalation,
Bandit: the Kingdom Army would arrange us as a mining team to mine on the shores of the void lake.
Aosta: And then?
Bandit: But that day...the void was supposedly in a state of inhalation, yet monsters just piled out of the void and went on a rampage.
Bandit: We were no match for the monsters. So many people died that day. I barely survived and escaped. Then, I saw a relic site.
Aosta: In Atlas? What kind of relic site?
Bandit: There's a door that connects to somewhere underground with some drawings on it. Didn't take a close look, but I still remember the location.
Aosta: How are you feeling now?
Bandit: Huh? Is the treatment over?
Bandit: Hmm...I do feel much better now.
Aosta: Good. Now take me to the relic site you mentioned before.
Bandit: Are you really in such a hurry? Right now the void is in a state of exhalation. There are monsters roaming around at all times; it's quite dangerous.
Bandit: M-M-Monsterssssss!!!
Aosta: So that's all they've got... does not constitute a threat.
Bandit: Whew~ that was scary. Thank goodness you're here...you're a graduate of the Rune Academy? Have you thought about enlisting in the army?
Aosta: Not interested.
Bandit: Weirdo.
Bandit: We're here. That's it.
Bandit: Hey, are you starting your research right now? Can you escort me back first, then come here?
Bandit: If you don't, I'm dead meat if I run into monsters again...
Aosta: No need to worry about that.
Bandit: What do you mean? Are you telling me that I won't run into monsters on my way back?
Aosta: More or less...
Aosta: If your body, after all the injuries it suffered from the bite, can even hold up until then, that is.
Aosta: That pattern on it...is it that of the Feather Clan?
Aosta: Looks like its unable to be opened directly...what about this?
Aosta: Damn it...
Aosta: Stop getting in my way!
Aosta: DAMNIT!!!!
